item.title: CVE-2022-3753|2024-08-03T01:20:57.583Z -- unknown -- evaluate
item.description: The Evaluate WordPress plugin through 1.0 does not sanitize and escapes some of its settings, which could allow high-privilege users such as admin to perform Stored Cross-Site Scripting attacks even when the unfiltered_html capability is disallowed (for example, in multisite setup).
